Firedrill tried to slow down, as he heard his passenger cough. The wings
rubbing against him didnt bother him to much, but he was not acostumed
to riding with a passenger, and since they were on ancient earth, didnt
think he would need to. He slowly followed Cliffjumper, keeping an eye
on him, as Beachcomber scouted ahead, easily jumping around on the rough
terrain.
